        <updateDate>2023-10-18T17:46:03Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Expanded Food Safety Investigation Act of &lt;/b&gt;&lt;b&gt;2023&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This bill provides that the Food and Drug Administration (FDA) may, under specified circumstances,&amp;nbsp;request access to a concentrated animal-feeding operation (i.e., a stabled or confined animal-feeding operation) to conduct microbial sampling.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Specifically, the bill allows the FDA to request access if the FDA determines that sampling is necessary to facilitate an investigation of a foodborne-illness outbreak, determine the cause of the outbreak, or address other public health needs.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The bill provides that such an operation shall be subject to penalties for refusing such a sampling.&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
